Bach called for patience and said the International Olympic Committee was fully focused on the challenge of staging the event during the coronavirus pandemicBach said the complexity of the Games had multiplied in the pandemic, and announced a "playbook" of measures, including social distancing and potential quarantines, intended to host them safelyOn Thursday, Tokyo's first Olympic test event this year, an artistic swimming competition scheduled for March, was postponed for two months because of travel restrictions